Sec. 26-27. Administration.
By implementing order, procedures for the advertisement, selection, and award of all agreements with Programming Partners shall be established. The implementing order shall be consistent with this article. The Department shall administer the Programming Partners process, which shall include at a minimum:
Recruitment Procedures for new Partners;
Measures for Existing Partners;
Criteria for Selection;
Partnership Agreement Types and Authorizations;
Required Information and Reporting;
Criteria for Performance Monitoring;
Measures to Address non-Performing Partners;
Procedures for Partnership Renewal;
Requirements for Participation in Fee Reduction/Scholarship Program;
Requirements for Background Checks of Volunteers;
Approval of Programming Partners Fees and Charges Schedules;
Mandatory Training Programs;
Opportunities for Recognition;
All Requests for Proposals for Programming Partners (RFPP) shall be prepared and issued by the Department. The Department shall receive and open such proposals, evaluate each proposal for responsiveness and qualifications, rank all proposals and shall make recommendations to the entity authorized by the Administrative Order to make the selection of award for a Programming Partner, as set forth herein. The type of agreement executed and level of authority for approval will be based upon the program purpose, use, term and amount of operating revenue and/or capital investment provided by the Programming Partner.
